{"url": "https://towardsdatascience.com/its-time-to-get-a-phd-in-coronavirus-cacf7e2e9e9f", "time": 1683005257.3610072, "path": "towardsdatascience.com/its-time-to-get-a-phd-in-coronavirus-cacf7e2e9e9f/", "webpage": {"metadata": {"title": "It\u2019s time to get a PhD in Coronavirus | by Ari Joury, PhD | Towards Data Science", "h1": "It\u2019s time to get a PhD in Coronavirus", "description": "Depending on where you live, you\u2019ve probably been suffering from Corona-related anxiety for the last few months, weeks, or days. And all the downplaying, the fake news, even the funny memes, tend to\u2026"}, "outgoing_paragraph_urls": [{"url": "https://www.coursera.org/learn/covid19-epidemiology/", "anchor_text": "This course", "paragraph_index": 4}, {"url": "https://www.coursera.org/learn/covid-19", "anchor_text": "this course", "paragraph_index": 6}, {"url": "https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/covid19-novel-coronavirus", "anchor_text": "This course", "paragraph_index": 9}, {"url": "https://openwho.org/courses/COVID-19-IPC-EN", "anchor_text": "official course", "paragraph_index": 12}, {"url": "https://openwho.org/courses/UNCT-COVID19-preparedness-and-response-EN", "anchor_text": "This course", "paragraph_index": 14}, {"url": "https://openwho.org/courses/introduction-to-ncov", "anchor_text": "This course", "paragraph_index": 17}, {"url": "https://arijoury.medium.com/membership", "anchor_text": "https://arijoury.medium.com/membership", "paragraph_index": 24}], "all_paragraphs": ["Depending on where you live, you\u2019ve probably been suffering from Corona-related anxiety for the last few months, weeks, or days. And all the downplaying, the fake news, even the funny memes, tend to heighten the angst, at least for me.", "If there is one cure for all this uncertainty, then it\u2019s knowledge. I wrote a story recently about how you can use these times of social distancing to educate yourself on Data Science. But what if you could curb your anxiety with knowledge about the same thing that causes it?", "Well, it turns out that there are actual online classes on Coronavirus. This is no B.S. \u2014 they\u2019re taught by world-class health and epidemiology researchers from the WHO, Imperial College London, Johns Hopkins University and more. You can even earn a certificate of achievement at the end of a few of them!", "I\u2019ll focus on courses in English, which are free of any fees and understandable for the general public. There are more courses for health professionals, but since I don\u2019t work in the field I don\u2019t feel qualified to evaluate those. The courses are presented in no particular order.", "This course focuses mostly on the epidemiological aspects of the outbreak: Its main focus is on how to collect and analyze the right data concerning an epidemic. Central questions are:", "The course also comes with a few practical tips on how to learn and connect with others during social isolation.", "While the aforementioned course focuses mainly on the quantitative aspects of the outbreak, this course also covers governmental and societal responses. It\u2019s also continuously updated as the pandemic evolves.", "Key points of this class are:", "time needed: ~12 hours, self-pacedstarting: any time", "This course has a stronger focus on health care, compared with the two previously described ones. The central pillars of the course are:", "Like many other courses, it is constantly updated to provide the latest we know about the virus. Upon completion, you can download a certificate of achievement to prove your success.", "time needed: ~1 hour, self-pacedstarting: any time", "This official course from the World Health Organization quickly sums up the current situation in the epidemic and the general guidelines for preparedness in these troubled times. Its core objectives are:", "time needed: ~2 hours, self-pacedstarting: any time", "This course is similar to the one described above but goes deeper into preparedness plans for epidemics. The core objectives are:", "If you achieve more than 80 percent of all points on graded assignments, you\u2019re are also eligible for a record of achievement.", "time needed: ~3 hours, self-pacedstarting: any time", "This course focuses on the biology and epidemiology of outbreaks like COVID-19, but also covers some aspects of response to a novel virus. The center points of the course are:", "It\u2019s continuously updated with the newest findings. At this moment, a certificate is not available, though one will be in the future.", "Social isolation and self-quarantine may seem like medieval responses in a time like ours. But since this Coronavirus is so new, this is the best that science has to offer at this point.", "That doesn\u2019t mean that you can\u2019t do anything. A first step is to educate yourself using trusted sources. Although a funny Corona-meme here and there can\u2019t do any harm in this anxiety-laden world\u2026", "Then, you might want to take your knowledge to the next level: Help your neighbors, especially the young, the elderly and the sick ones. Look after children in your area or go shopping for someone else. These are not the times to be selfish.", "Maybe these courses won\u2019t be enough to get you a PhD in Coronavirus. But they\u2019ll surely get you one in human greatness.", "Your home for data science. A Medium publication sharing concepts, ideas and codes.", "Lost in my thoughts, mostly about tech. https://arijoury.medium.com/membership"], "all_outgoing_urls": [{"url": "https://rsci.app.link/?%24canonical_url=https%3A%2F%2Fmedium.com%2Fp%2Fcacf7e2e9e9f&%7Efeature=LoOpenInAppButton&%7Echannel=ShowPostUnderCollection&source=---two_column_layout_nav----------------------------------", "anchor_text": "Open in app"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=register&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Ftowardsdatascience.com%2Fits-time-to-get-a-phd-in-coronavirus-cacf7e2e9e9f&source=post_page---two_column_layout_nav-----------------------global_n